          <actionDate>2016-12-12</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>States Against Drunk Driving Act of 2016 or the SADD Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill authorizes supplemental funds under the Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant program for states that: (1) report at least 90% of DUI convictions, and (2) have in effect a law or policy that requires a DUI conviction to be taken into account for purposes of an enhanced criminal sentence under state law. </p> <p>The term &quot;DUI conviction&quot; means a criminal conviction for operating a motor vehicle under the influence of a drug or alcohol.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
